# Speak Draft AI — Coding Standards

## General Principles

- **TypeScript everywhere** — no `any`, no implicit types. Always infer or explicitly type.
- **Server Components by default** — only use `"use client"` when you need interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs.
- **Convex functions are the backend** — never call the database directly from API routes. All DB logic lives in `/convex`.
- **Small, focused files** — one concern per file. If a file exceeds ~200 lines, split it.
- **Named exports only** — no default exports except for Next.js pages/layouts.
- **No hardcoded strings** — all content types, languages, credit costs in `/lib/constants.ts`.

---

## File & Folder Conventions

```
/app/(dashboard)/briefs/page.tsx     # Page (Server Component)
/app/(dashboard)/briefs/_components/ # Page-level components (not reused)
/components/brief/BriefCard.tsx      # Shared components
/convex/briefs.ts                    # All brief DB queries/mutations
/lib/hubspot.ts                      # External service clients
/lib/constants.ts                    # Enums, maps, credit costs
/hooks/useBrief.ts                   # Client-side hooks
/types/index.ts                      # Shared TypeScript types
```

