## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ Always handle async errors explicitly
const result = await generateDraft(brief).catch((err) => {
  Sentry.captureException(err)
  return null
})
if (!result) return <ErrorState message="Draft generation failed" />

// ✅ Convex mutations throw on failure — wrap in try/catch in client
try {
  await createBrief({ title, contentType })
} catch (err) {
  toast.error("Failed to create brief")
}

// ✅ Never swallow errors silently
// ❌ Bad
try { ... } catch (e) {}
```

